comments.body:
I looked at all the solutions, and I needed getApplicationContext but could not find such a function. So, as you know, Uri does not have a parse function. I have stored my image files in Resources\\drawable\\animal00.png" and Resources\\raw\\animal00.png" Thanks for your reply.

```cs
if (IsAndroid())
{
    String pkgName = getApplicationContext().getPackageName();
    Uri path = Uri.parse("android.resource://" + pkgName + "/" + R.drawable.icon);
    Uri otherPath = Uri.parse("android.resource://" + pkgName + "/drawable/icon");
```
